article.headline: Auburn 84, Colorado State 54
article.story: AUBURN, Ala. (AP) -- Kyle Davis scored a career-high 21 points and nine rebounds and Marco Killingsworth added 19 points and seven rebounds to lead Auburn over Colorado State 84-54 Monday night. The Tigers (5-0) dominated the boards 37-26 and shot 53 percent from the floor, turning the game into a blowout. Auburn lead 36-18 at halftime and the Rams (2-2) never got closer than 18 points in the second half. Davis was 7 of 9 from the field and 7 of 10 in free throws. Ian Young made three 3-pointers and added 13 points for Auburn, while Nathan Watson hit two from the 3-point range. The Tigers had widened their lead by 33 points in the second half after two shots by Davis and 3-pointers by Watson and Lollar, making it 78-45 with 4 minutes left in the game. Matt Nelson led the Rams with 12 points and Freddy Robinson added 11. The Tigers capitalized on Colorado State's sloppiness throughout the game, scoring 28 points off their 23 turnovers while holding the Rams to 35 percent shooting.
